{
  "readme": {
    "type": "root",
    "children": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "value": "A "
          },
          {
            "type": "link",
            "url": "https://qiime2.org",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "value": "QIIME 2"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "value": " plugin for generating and working with kmers from biological sequence information."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "depth": 2,
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "value": "Installation instructions"
          }
        ],
        "identifier": "installation-instructions",
        "label": "Installation instructions",
        "html_id": "installation-instructions",
        "implicit": true
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "value": "The easiest way to install q2-kmerizer is to install it directly into an existing installation of "
          },
          {
            "type": "link",
            "url": "https://qiime2.org/",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "value": "QIIME 2"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "value": " (amplicon distribution version 2024.10 or later). If you have the QIIME 2 amplicon distribution installed, activate your environment and run the following to install q2-kmerizer into this environment:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "code",
        "lang": "",
        "value": "pip install q2_kmerizer@git+https://github.com/bokulich-lab/q2-kmerizer.git@main"
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "value": "And refresh your cache:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "code",
        "lang": "",
        "value": "qiime dev refresh-cache"
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "value": "If the installation worked correctly, the following command should display a description of the plugin in your terminal:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "code",
        "lang": "",
        "value": "qiime kmerizer --help"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "depth": 3,
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "value": "Installation of stable release"
          }
        ],
        "identifier": "installation-of-stable-release",
        "label": "Installation of stable release",
        "html_id": "installation-of-stable-release",
        "implicit": true
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "value": "If you do not already have QIIME 2 installed, you can follow these instructions to install the QIIME 2 amplicon distribution as well as the latest stable version of q2-kmerizer."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "link",
            "url": "https://conda.io/miniconda.html",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "value": "Miniconda"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "value": " provides the "
          },
          {
            "type": "inlineCode",
            "value": "conda"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "value": " environment and package manager, and is currently the only supported way to install QIIME 2.\nFollow the instructions for downloading and installing Miniconda."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "value": "After installing Miniconda and opening a new terminal, make sure you’re running the latest version of "
          },
          {
            "type": "inlineCode",
            "value": "conda"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "value": ":"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "code",
        "lang": "bash",
        "value": "conda update conda"
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "value": "Now use conda to install q2-kmerizer and QIIME 2:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "code",
        "lang": "shell",
        "value": "conda env create -n kmerizer-stable --file https://raw.githubusercontent.com/bokulich-lab/q2-kmerizer/main/environment-files/q2-kmerizer-qiime2-amplicon-2025.4.yml"
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "value": "After this completes, activate the new environment you created by running:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "code",
        "lang": "shell",
        "value": "conda activate kmerizer-stable"
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "value": "Then refresh your cache and test as shown above."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "depth": 3,
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "value": "Install development version of "
          },
          {
            "type": "inlineCode",
            "value": "q2-kmerizer"
          }
        ],
        "identifier": "install-development-version-of-q2-kmerizer",
        "label": "Install development version of q2-kmerizer",
        "html_id": "install-development-version-of-q2-kmerizer",
        "implicit": true
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "value": "If you wish to use the development version of q2-kmerizer, e.g., to develop new features in your fork or to contribute to the main branch, follow these instructions."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "value": "First, you must have conda installed, as described above."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "value": "Next, clone the repository and move into the top-level "
          },
          {
            "type": "inlineCode",
            "value": "q2-kmerizer"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "value": " directory. NOTE: make sure your current working directory is a location where you want to install this plugin!"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "code",
        "lang": "",
        "value": "git clone https://github.com/bokulich-lab/q2-kmerizer.git\ncd q2-kmerizer"
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "value": "Then, run:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "code",
        "lang": "shell",
        "value": "conda env create -n q2-kmerizer-dev --file ./environment-files/q2-kmerizer-qiime2-amplicon-2025.4.yml"
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "value": "After this completes, activate the new environment you created by running:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "code",
        "lang": "shell",
        "value": "conda activate q2-kmerizer-dev"
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "value": "Finally, run:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "code",
        "lang": "shell",
        "value": "make install"
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "value": "Then refresh your cache and test as shown above."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "depth": 2,
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "value": "Examples"
          }
        ],
        "identifier": "examples",
        "label": "Examples",
        "html_id": "examples",
        "implicit": true
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "value": "As an example test, we will use data from "
          },
          {
            "type": "link",
            "url": "https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/27912057",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "value": "Sampson et al, 2016"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "value": ", a study testing whether the fecal microbiome contributed to the development of Parkinson’s Disease (PD)."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "value": "First we will download the test data:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "code",
        "lang": "",
        "value": "wget https://data.qiime2.org/2024.10/tutorials/pd-mice/sample_metadata.tsv\nwget https://docs.qiime2.org/2024.10/data/tutorials/pd-mice/dada2_table.qza\nwget https://docs.qiime2.org/2024.10/data/tutorials/pd-mice/dada2_rep_set.qza"
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "value": "We can count kmer frequencies per sample with this command:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "code",
        "lang": "",
        "value": "qiime kmerizer seqs-to-kmers \\\n    --i-sequences dada2_rep_set.qza \\\n    --i-table dada2_table.qza \\\n    --o-kmer-table kmer_table.qza \\\n    --p-max-features 5000"
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "value": "Or run this pipeline to count kmer frequencies, calculate diversity metrics, and create an interactive scatterplot with the results:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "code",
        "lang": "",
        "value": "qiime kmerizer core-metrics \\\n    --i-sequences dada2_rep_set.qza \\\n    --i-table dada2_table.qza \\\n    --p-sampling-depth 1000 \\\n    --m-metadata-file sample_metadata.tsv \\\n    --p-color-by-group donor \\\n    --p-max-features 5000 \\\n    --output-dir core-metrics/"
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "value": "Both of these actions output a frequency table that contains kmer counts per sample. This can be used like any other frequency table and passed to any action in QIIME 2 that accepts a frequency table (except for those that also require additional inputs that must match the features in the table, e.g., that require a taxonomy). For example, we can run a pipeline to train a Random Forest classifier and test on a hold-out subset of the dataset (note: this analysis is done purely for demonstrative purposes; the sample size in this test dataset is much smaller than would be required for a robust supervised learning analysis, and proper replicate handling should be done to avoid data leakage)."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "code",
        "lang": "",
        "value": "qiime sample-classifier classify-samples \\\n    --i-table kmer_table.qza \\\n    --m-metadata-file sample_metadata.tsv \\\n    --m-metadata-column donor \\\n    --output-dir sample-classifier/"
      },
